  "commentary": "With SPX at 6767.6 trading in the amplifying zone between max negative gamma at 6750 (-48.8B) and the stabilizing wall at 6800 (+39.8B), dealers are currently buying this dip as they're short gamma and forced to hedge delta dynamically. The massive negative GEX concentration from 6750-6765 creates a dangerous amplification pocket where any selling pressure will force dealers to sell more, while a push toward 6800 would trigger dealer selling into strength as they hit the positive gamma wall. The 30%+ GEX surge indicates rapidly shifting positioning, making the 6750 and 6800 strikes critical inflection points for momentum shifts.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6750 and 6800 with big moves likely if either level breaks.",
